rich, it is full of history.

00:02:13.400 --> 00:02:16.280
This linguistic,
beautiful language

00:02:16.280 --> 00:02:18.470
is something that I've had--

00:02:18.470 --> 00:02:23.676
and it's been part of American
culture for over 200 years.

00:02:23.676 --> 00:02:27.750
It has been down since
back in native times

00:02:27.750 --> 00:02:29.490
and has transitioned
as a language,

00:02:29.490 --> 00:02:33.040
like many languages do,
over a 200 year period.

00:02:33.040 --> 00:02:37.830
Now there are formal
language systems, as we know,

00:02:37.830 --> 00:02:42.060
and how language develops
is by the culture,

00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:45.670
the community, sharing
knowledge, experiences.

00:02:45.670 --> 00:02:48.360
And therefore
emerges further uses

00:02:48.360 --> 00:02:51.930
of language, language
choices, and signs,

00:02:51.930 --> 00:02:55.290
and those are based on
culture that were predating

00:02:55.290 --> 00:02:58.680
those currently using it.

00:02:58.680 --> 00:03:03.100
American Sign Language has five
distinct and unique parameters.

00:03:05.770 --> 00:03:08.830
I'm going to show you these
to help you understand

00:03:08.830 --> 00:03:11.680
how we communicate and
how it has developed

00:03:11.680 --> 00:03:14.020
using a cultural framework.

00:03:14.020 --> 00:03:15.940
The first is hand shape.

00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:17.530
So, obviously,
for sign language,

00:03:17.530 --> 00:03:20.546
you need a hand shape
like this or this.

00:03:20.546 --> 00:03:23.480
[LAUGHTER]

00:03:23.480 --> 00:03:25.850
So that is the
shape of your hand--

00:03:25.850 --> 00:03:29.500
it is very crucial.

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:36.160
Now, which hand shape you use
really is dependent on context.

00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:37.990
Second parameter is location.

00:03:37.990 --> 00:03:40.130
Where is that hand going to?

00:03:40.130 --> 00:03:43.450
Now there are various
categories within that.

00:03:43.450 --> 00:03:48.040
As an example, you
can start up here

00:03:48.040 --> 00:03:53.300
in this location, versus this
location, versus this location,

00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:57.190
versus here, versus out here.

00:03:57.190 --> 00:03:58.900
All the signs that
we'll be doing--

00:03:58.900 --> 00:04:03.100
and you'll see-- have
that specific objection.

00:04:03.100 --> 00:04:05.320
Objective in using that
location about what it's

00:04:05.320 --> 00:04:07.390
going to indicate, and
the various categories

00:04:07.390 --> 00:04:09.520
and what it means.

00:04:09.520 --> 00:04:13.310
The next parameter is movement.

00:04:13.310 --> 00:04:18.582
So remember we have the hand
shape, we have a location,

00:04:18.582 --> 00:04:20.540
and now we're going to
put some movement to it.

00:04:20.540 --> 00:04:22.060
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:22.060 --> 00:04:23.060
Now what does this mean?

00:04:23.060 --> 00:04:24.250
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:24.250 --> 00:04:26.630
Hello?

00:04:26.630 --> 00:04:27.650
Right?

00:04:27.650 --> 00:04:29.870
So there's where movement
is the characteristic

00:04:29.870 --> 00:04:31.747
within the language--
that parameter.

00:04:31.747 --> 00:04:32.580
Now what about this?

00:04:32.580 --> 00:04:33.200
What does this mean?

00:04:33.200 --> 00:04:33.700
- Stop.

00:04:33.700 --> 00:04:35.690
- Stop.

00:04:35.690 --> 00:04:37.690
- That means stop, right?

00:04:37.690 --> 00:04:38.770
Or, whoa.

00:04:38.770 --> 00:04:41.440
Hold on.

00:04:41.440 --> 00:04:44.320
Or you can be welcoming someone.

00:04:44.320 --> 00:04:47.260
So again, movement is
such a crucial aspect

00:04:47.260 --> 00:04:49.960
of language in its expression.

00:04:49.960 --> 00:04:52.930
So the next parameter
is palm orientation.

00:04:56.900 --> 00:05:01.710
As I just demonstrated
as an example,

00:05:01.710 --> 00:05:05.900
using this hand shape,
which would mean, hey, wait,

00:05:05.900 --> 00:05:08.600
versus this, changing
my palm orientation,

00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:13.390
could say you, or
only you, or wait.

00:05:13.390 --> 00:05:19.530
It's the same movement, but
the palm orientation now

00:05:19.530 --> 00:05:23.290
indicates a different
meaning in the language.

00:05:23.290 --> 00:05:25.600
So again, palm
orientation is crucial.

00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:30.170
And finally, but last but not
least, is facial expressions.

00:05:30.170 --> 00:05:34.560
This is how you communicate
feelings, thoughts--

00:05:34.560 --> 00:05:38.440
also gives a sense of time.

00:05:38.440 --> 00:05:42.440
Also, as an example, using this.

00:05:42.440 --> 00:05:45.815
This is an example of
indicating someone walking.

00:05:45.815 --> 00:05:49.620
[LAUGHTER]

00:05:49.620 --> 00:05:51.000
You get the picture.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:52.018
This is a long walk.

00:05:52.018 --> 00:05:53.310
Someone's going to be dragging.

00:05:56.940 --> 00:05:58.860
So simply by that
facial expression,

00:05:58.860 --> 00:06:01.140
we've been able to evoke
if someone is having

00:06:01.140 --> 00:06:03.870
a good day, or a bad day.

00:06:03.870 --> 00:06:09.290
So all those are parameters
that are so crucial.

00:06:09.290 --> 00:06:12.290
And by the selection
of those parameters,

00:06:12.290 --> 00:06:17.750
can then craft your message
and convey your culture,

00:06:17.750 --> 00:06:20.269
your personality, your tone.

00:06:20.269 --> 00:06:21.686
So now I'm going
to go back to one

00:06:21.686 --> 00:06:25.340
of those parameters
about location.

00:06:25.340 --> 00:06:29.270
These two are very unique along
with these other few locations

00:06:29.270 --> 00:06:32.470
associated with gender.

00:06:32.470 --> 00:06:34.570
It's associated with
male and female.

00:06:34.570 --> 00:06:38.350
Gender has already been
assigned to those locations.

00:06:38.350 --> 00:06:40.780
Male is here.

00:06:40.780 --> 00:06:45.850
Any male oriented sign is
typically in this location.

00:06:45.850 --> 00:06:47.603
But why do you think up here?

00:06:47.603 --> 00:06:49.770
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:06:49.770 --> 00:06:51.552
- Any guesses?

00:06:51.552 --> 00:06:54.230
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:06:54.230 --> 00:06:57.130
- The brain, the
head, intellect.

00:06:57.130 --> 00:06:58.460
What else what else you got?

00:06:58.460 --> 00:06:58.960
- Hats.

00:06:58.960 --> 00:06:59.990
- Hats.

00:06:59.990 --> 00:07:01.790
OK.

00:07:01.790 --> 00:07:02.290
Yeah.

00:07:02.290 --> 00:07:05.590
So back in time where
gentlemen were wearing hats.

00:07:05.590 --> 00:07:09.250
Showing someone is a thinker,
as opposed to being emotive.

00:07:09.250 --> 00:07:11.290
Logic, intellect,
and, of course,

00:07:11.290 --> 00:07:13.120
going on with those
other adjectives.

00:07:13.120 --> 00:07:15.410
But again, that
orientation, that location.

00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:16.410
Now female.

00:07:16.410 --> 00:07:19.220
Any guesses what
location that would be?

00:07:19.220 --> 00:07:20.080
Let me see.

00:07:20.080 --> 00:07:20.913
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:07:20.913 --> 00:07:21.800
- Oh, interesting.

00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:23.380
I see a few.

00:07:23.380 --> 00:07:24.520
Nice, that's interesting.

00:07:24.520 --> 00:07:28.680
Why did you guys pick this as a
location I saw in the audience?

00:07:28.680 --> 00:07:33.430
Emotion, love,
nurturer, caregiver.

00:07:33.430 --> 00:07:37.120
It's actually this
location right here.

00:07:37.120 --> 00:07:38.920
This is the location for female.

00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:42.940
So again, female oriented
signs of that love,

00:07:42.940 --> 00:07:47.710
emotion, nurturing, typically
have these two locations.

00:07:47.710 --> 00:07:52.040
But primarily on the chin here.

00:07:52.040 --> 00:07:56.720
So there are subsets within just
the idea of location, which is,

00:07:56.720 --> 00:07:58.210
of course, indicating binary.

00:07:58.210 --> 00:08:02.580
You have boy, as girl,
because the bonnet.

00:08:02.580 --> 00:08:05.260
Boys because of
the baseball cap.

00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:07.358
So this is the sign for girl.

00:08:07.358 --> 00:08:09.150
So this is the kind of
the language we use.

00:08:11.078 --> 00:08:12.620
So I'm going to give
you guys-- we're

00:08:12.620 --> 00:08:15.090
going to do a little
hands-on activity.

00:08:15.090 --> 00:08:16.590
So we're going to
pick a hand shape.

00:08:16.590 --> 00:08:18.090
Let's do this hand
shape right here.

00:08:18.090 --> 00:08:21.072
So I want everyone to copy
me, you in the audience.

00:08:21.072 --> 00:08:22.530
We're going to give
you a movement.

00:08:27.620 --> 00:08:32.169
Now the term is going to be mom.

00:08:32.169 --> 00:08:36.429
Where do you think that hand
shape movement should go?

00:08:36.429 --> 00:08:38.830
Show me.

00:08:38.830 --> 00:08:41.549
Like this?

00:08:41.549 --> 00:08:43.549
Perfect.

00:08:43.549 --> 00:08:45.500
Now, for the term
dad, where do you

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:48.200
think that hand shape
would go as far as location

00:08:48.200 --> 00:08:49.100
is concerned?

00:08:49.100 --> 00:08:50.210
Here?

00:08:50.210 --> 00:08:51.320
Exactly.

00:08:51.320 --> 00:08:53.590
Great job.

00:08:53.590 --> 00:08:58.760
So, similar hand shape, similar
movement, different location.

00:08:58.760 --> 00:09:01.450
There demonstrating
the role of father

00:09:01.450 --> 00:09:08.040
versus mother, boy
versus girl, grandparents

00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:10.950
or grandpa, grandma.

00:09:10.950 --> 00:09:11.880
What about Grandpa?

00:09:11.880 --> 00:09:13.340
What do you think?

00:09:13.340 --> 00:09:14.200
[LAUGHTER]

00:09:14.200 --> 00:09:15.600
Oh, wow yeah.

00:09:15.600 --> 00:09:17.920
Right off the bat.

00:09:17.920 --> 00:09:20.776
And this would be
grandmother, or grandma.

00:09:20.776 --> 00:09:22.240
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

00:09:22.240 --> 00:09:25.270
- Notice that movement
in that location.

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:29.130
So that is a systematic way in
American Sign Language using

00:09:29.130 --> 00:09:31.110
that movement and location.

00:09:31.110 --> 00:09:35.160
So now, in a generation,
fast-forwarding to now,

00:09:35.160 --> 00:09:37.800
where we have the spectrum
of male and female

00:09:37.800 --> 00:09:41.220
that we're looking at, how
does this impact sign language

00:09:41.220 --> 00:09:43.830
and how it's expressed,
where things are not

00:09:43.830 --> 00:09:44.862
already assigned?

00:09:44.862 --> 00:09:46.570
So as a deaf community,
this is something

00:09:46.570 --> 00:09:49.620
we're starting to look at.

00:09:49.620 --> 00:09:53.340
What is a sign to
identify a gender?

00:09:53.340 --> 00:09:56.480
And other signs that we
might not have signs for,

00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:58.380
that have not yet
been established.

00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:08.810
So, for example, the
term transgender.

00:10:08.810 --> 00:10:09.640
The sign is this.

00:10:14.540 --> 00:10:15.930
And notice that location.

00:10:15.930 --> 00:10:20.940
Why do you think this
location was used?

00:10:20.940 --> 00:10:23.920
It's there to indicate the soul.

00:10:23.920 --> 00:10:28.490
The inner workings of
someone's heart, their soul.

00:10:28.490 --> 00:10:30.140
All the rest is a shell.

00:10:30.140 --> 00:10:32.570
Everything else that's
been biologically assigned,

00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:34.730
but to a person's soul.

00:10:34.730 --> 00:10:37.940
And so, when they have
that transformation,

00:10:37.940 --> 00:10:40.390
that's where that movement
comes in that location.

00:10:40.390 --> 00:10:42.260
A beautiful sign.

00:10:42.260 --> 00:10:43.070
Now the hand shape.

00:10:43.070 --> 00:10:43.570
Like this.

00:10:48.150 --> 00:10:51.270
That hand shape, along
with that movement,

00:10:51.270 --> 00:10:54.330
has a very unique
theme, a distinct theme.

00:10:57.352 --> 00:10:58.810
Now the sign for
beautiful is this.

00:11:01.252 --> 00:11:02.960
Notice that hand shape
and that movement?

00:11:06.690 --> 00:11:07.515
You can sign grow.

00:11:12.290 --> 00:11:15.500
Also a part of that
same sign, culture.

00:11:18.680 --> 00:11:23.930
So that hand shape in itself
has a very rich history,

00:11:23.930 --> 00:11:27.270
and such deep
meaning and context.

00:11:27.270 --> 00:11:31.370
So, to use that sign and
assign it to who I am,

00:11:31.370 --> 00:11:33.350
how do I identify.

00:11:33.350 --> 00:11:36.020
And that's where the origin
for transgender, and that

00:11:36.020 --> 00:11:38.100
sign in our community.

00:11:38.100 --> 00:11:41.480
Another term-- non-binary.

00:11:41.480 --> 00:11:44.120
We've heard that today.

00:11:44.120 --> 00:11:47.210
From a hearing,
non-signing perspective,

00:11:47.210 --> 00:11:50.510
you have the words
male, female, binary.

00:11:50.510 --> 00:11:53.000
Those systems have
been in place.

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:55.820
And those who are
nonconforming, that's

00:11:55.820 --> 00:11:58.420
where we come up
with the word non,

00:11:58.420 --> 00:12:05.410
to then show the contrast of
that standard nonconformity.

00:12:05.410 --> 00:12:09.040
Non-binary-- to disassociate
from that concept

00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:12.970
of the standard stereotype,
or that established systematic

00:12:12.970 --> 00:12:15.290
terminology.

00:12:15.290 --> 00:12:18.020
And again, in time, there
will be new identities

00:12:18.020 --> 00:12:19.610
that will continue to come up.

00:12:19.610 --> 00:12:22.520
But the first step and
stage is to disassociate

00:12:22.520 --> 00:12:25.790
from the norm in those
cultural words and labels

00:12:25.790 --> 00:12:27.640
as we know them.

00:12:27.640 --> 00:12:32.050
And that is also impacting
American Sign Language.

00:12:32.050 --> 00:12:34.120
There are things that we
might not have a sign--

00:12:34.120 --> 00:12:37.210
and there are various rules,
grammatical, linguistic rules,

00:12:37.210 --> 00:12:38.790
that are associated
to sign language.

00:12:38.790 --> 00:12:41.020
Remember, you have
to have a location.

00:12:41.020 --> 00:12:45.070
Now think about this neutral
space right here as a location.

00:12:45.070 --> 00:12:48.310
As you can see, it's
disassociated from my body.

00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:51.340
So, as an example,
you have non-binary,

00:12:51.340 --> 00:12:53.530
or, just for short,
the acronym NB,

00:12:53.530 --> 00:12:56.950
as in American Sign Language,
we'll just use that short.

00:12:56.950 --> 00:13:01.630
But out in space, as you can
see, is a different location.

00:13:01.630 --> 00:13:04.315
So this is something that's
continuing to evolve.

00:13:09.010 --> 00:13:12.975
As we saw hats and bonnets
and various fashion items

00:13:12.975 --> 00:13:14.350
that we've just
talked about have

00:13:14.350 --> 00:13:18.040
changed till today, we also have
that same thing with language

00:13:18.040 --> 00:13:20.410
and it's a beautiful
thing to see.

00:13:20.410 --> 00:13:23.710
We have one other activity
before I'm out of my time here.

