privilege for the language I

00:16:09.480 --> 00:16:11.310
choose to use.

00:16:11.310 --> 00:16:14.580
For this presentation
and its perspective,

00:16:14.580 --> 00:16:21.240
I will be using the terms
female as a umbrella term.

00:16:21.240 --> 00:16:23.130
So, I mean all of
those who identify.

00:16:23.130 --> 00:16:26.220
So I want to recognize as a
white woman how society views

00:16:26.220 --> 00:16:30.270
me, how society views
women, and women of color,

00:16:30.270 --> 00:16:32.220
and that discrepancy.

00:16:32.220 --> 00:16:36.940
So just as a whole,
to keep that in mind.

00:16:36.940 --> 00:16:38.670
Also, I want to clarify
some terminology

00:16:38.670 --> 00:16:40.110
that I might be using.

00:16:40.110 --> 00:16:43.290
I will state the word
deaf, which is an umbrella

00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:47.233
term because it is a very
diverse cultural community,

00:16:47.233 --> 00:16:48.900
and they all use
American Sign Language.

00:16:48.900 --> 00:16:52.280
So that can indicate someone
who is deaf, deaf-blind, someone

00:16:52.280 --> 00:16:53.610
who is hard of hearing.

00:16:53.610 --> 00:16:55.950
But again, that language
that they're using

00:16:55.950 --> 00:16:57.570
is American Sign Language.

00:16:57.570 --> 00:16:59.100
But to interact
in the world, they

00:16:59.100 --> 00:17:03.520
may need to use an interpreter
for someone who does not sign.

00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:08.140
Also I might speak about
male, and female, transgender

00:17:08.140 --> 00:17:09.972
as well, and cisgender.

00:17:12.869 --> 00:17:16.520
And I have two
scenarios and anecdotes

00:17:16.520 --> 00:17:19.190
to show what it looks like
as an American Sign Language

00:17:19.190 --> 00:17:23.480
interpreter, whether it's in
public or behind closed doors.

00:17:23.480 --> 00:17:24.349
Here's the scenario.

00:17:24.349 --> 00:17:26.359
As a staff interpreter,
I was working

00:17:26.359 --> 00:17:27.890
at Boston Children's Hospital.

00:17:27.890 --> 00:17:29.900
There was an appointment,
which I went in.

00:17:29.900 --> 00:17:33.050
The provider and the doctor was
there speaking to the patient.

00:17:33.050 --> 00:17:34.740
This is post-op.

00:17:34.740 --> 00:17:37.130
And then was saying, hey,
you gotta get off your butt--

00:17:37.130 --> 00:17:40.482
and the doctor, as he said
