00:27:45.925 --> 00:27:48.893
wrong with him, all of these
without drawing undue attention

00:27:48.893 --> 00:27:50.810
to the fact that their
communications with you

00:27:50.810 --> 00:27:52.160
are mediated through a female.

00:27:55.150 --> 00:27:57.810
For this next section, I'd like
to borrow from the LifeCourse

00:27:57.810 --> 00:27:59.610
Framework in the field
of public health.

00:27:59.610 --> 00:28:01.740
And if this is
unfamiliar to you,

00:28:01.740 --> 00:28:05.890
the basic premise is that all
factors, genetics, nutrition,

00:28:05.890 --> 00:28:09.330
social relationships,
financial security, exposure

00:28:09.330 --> 00:28:11.833
to environmental toxins
and the like, all of these

00:28:11.833 --> 00:28:13.500
have a cumulative
impact on one's health

00:28:13.500 --> 00:28:14.800
throughout their lifetime.

00:28:14.800 --> 00:28:16.710
And so, what we
experience today as

00:28:16.710 --> 00:28:18.960
chronic physical and
mental conditions have

00:28:18.960 --> 00:28:22.110
root causes that date way back.

00:28:22.110 --> 00:28:24.190
Now, if we take that
LifeCourse Framework

00:28:24.190 --> 00:28:26.108
and apply it to the
life of a deaf male,

00:28:26.108 --> 00:28:28.150
for whom communication
with non-deaf individuals,

00:28:28.150 --> 00:28:29.567
as we've discussed
time and again,

00:28:29.567 --> 00:28:32.230
is mediated through a
female ASL interpreter.

00:28:32.230 --> 00:28:34.540
I want to know, what's
the cumulative impact,

00:28:34.540 --> 00:28:36.138
and can we even name it?

00:28:36.138 --> 00:28:38.680
Please note that the following
list is not exhaustive, nor is

00:28:38.680 --> 00:28:39.700
it true for everyone.

00:28:39.700 --> 00:28:41.980
Interpreters are not
employed in all situations

00:28:41.980 --> 00:28:43.330
or to the same degree.

00:28:43.330 --> 00:28:46.270
I'm simply using
these as exemplars.

00:28:46.270 --> 00:28:48.190
Let's start with a
deaf boy's childhood.

00:28:48.190 --> 00:28:50.620
Consider his education
and his extracurriculars.

00:28:50.620 --> 00:28:53.950
Please also note, that 87% of
deaf children in the United

00:28:53.950 --> 00:28:56.710
States are not sent to schools
with deaf peers, deaf role

00:28:56.710 --> 00:28:59.680
models, and others who are like
them, in a visually accessible

00:28:59.680 --> 00:29:01.030
educational environment.

00:29:01.030 --> 00:29:04.300
Instead they're sent to
schools with peers and adults

00:29:04.300 --> 00:29:07.060
who are not like them, and their
entire educational experience

00:29:07.060 --> 00:29:10.150
is mediated through a likely
white female interpreter.

00:29:10.150 --> 00:29:13.170
So these are the public
schools that they're in.

00:29:13.170 --> 00:29:13.920
So think about it.

00:29:13.920 --> 00:29:16.643
Your classroom activities, your
group work with peers, maybe

00:29:16.643 --> 00:29:18.310
even your social
connections with peers,

00:29:18.310 --> 00:29:21.620
all mediated through an adult
woman as a young deaf boy.

00:29:21.620 --> 00:29:24.120
But it's not just about the
boys lived experience or other's

00:29:24.120 --> 00:29:25.405
experience of him.

00:29:25.405 --> 00:29:27.030
How does the presence
of an adult woman

00:29:27.030 --> 00:29:30.420
impact him in ways that we
might not even be able to name?

00:29:30.420 --> 00:29:32.787
That's what I want to know.

00:29:32.787 --> 00:29:33.870
Let's look at adolescence.

00:29:33.870 --> 00:29:35.880
Let's take some
common experiences.

00:29:35.880 --> 00:29:38.345
Driver's Ed, internship
interviews or placements,

00:29:38.345 --> 00:29:39.720
meetings with
guidance counselors

00:29:39.720 --> 00:29:43.350
to talk about your future plans,
athletics, if that's your bag.

00:29:43.350 --> 00:29:45.600
How is an adolescent
boy's experience

00:29:45.600 --> 00:29:47.250
shaped by working
with an adult female

00:29:47.250 --> 00:29:49.050
for these rites of passage?

00:29:49.050 --> 00:29:50.610
What about how others treat him?

00:29:50.610 --> 00:29:52.110
What opportunities he's offered?

00:29:52.110 --> 00:29:54.360
What he learns about
his changing body,

00:29:54.360 --> 00:29:56.010
about networking,
or getting ahead

00:29:56.010 --> 00:29:59.330
in love, life, and his career?

00:29:59.330 --> 00:30:02.220
As a young adult, what
are the social, financial,

00:30:02.220 --> 00:30:05.780
and academic impacts of having
a female in your college classes

00:30:05.780 --> 00:30:07.670
or in your vocational training?

00:30:07.670 --> 00:30:08.490
Or in Greek life?

00:30:08.490 --> 00:30:08.990
Right?

00:30:08.990 --> 00:30:11.360
All you want to do is make a
solid impression as a pledge,

00:30:11.360 --> 00:30:12.980
or shoot the shit with
your fraternity brothers,

00:30:12.980 --> 00:30:14.897
and then here's this
woman in the middle of it

00:30:14.897 --> 00:30:17.360
all who very well may
be your parents age.

00:30:19.965 --> 00:30:22.090
Look, I'm not saying these
poor deaf guys-- right--

00:30:22.090 --> 00:30:23.173
they have to work with us.

00:30:23.173 --> 00:30:25.030
And I'm certainly
not saying deaf men

00:30:25.030 --> 00:30:28.225
and female ASL interpreters
shouldn't be working together.

00:30:28.225 --> 00:30:30.100
I'm just arguing that
society's view of women

00:30:30.100 --> 00:30:33.130
has short-term and long-term
impacts on these deaf boys

00:30:33.130 --> 00:30:35.380
and these men and their
lifetime earning potential,

00:30:35.380 --> 00:30:37.807
their social mobility, and
perhaps even their health.

00:30:40.550 --> 00:30:43.127
Lastly, for social services
and health care, many of us

00:30:43.127 --> 00:30:44.960
can agree that we feel
more comfortable when

00:30:44.960 --> 00:30:46.835
we're working with a
health care provider who

00:30:46.835 --> 00:30:48.080
shares our same gender.

00:30:48.080 --> 00:30:50.370
Deaf men are not afforded
this luxury though.

00:30:50.370 --> 00:30:54.110
It is more than likely
that at some point

00:30:54.110 --> 00:30:56.670
they will have a female present
for their consultations,

00:30:56.670 --> 00:30:59.840
or for other health care
encounters that many of us

00:30:59.840 --> 00:31:02.720
can agree we'd rather not have
someone of the opposite gender

00:31:02.720 --> 00:31:04.300
in.

00:31:04.300 --> 00:31:04.800
OK.

00:31:04.800 --> 00:31:06.137
And so here we are.

